HEADWORD: hitless
<hw>hitless</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Baseball)</fld>
<def>Having no hits scored; -- of a baseball game (or the pitching) in
which a pitcher allows the opponent no hits; <as>as, a <ex>hitless</ex>
game</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> no-hit.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having no points scored.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> scoreless, goalless.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hit man</ent>⟦br⟧
